le="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">become</span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.75pt"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">a</span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.7pt"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">long</span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.75pt"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">and</span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.75pt"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">expensive</span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.7pt"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">process.</span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.75pt"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">CSS</span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">was</span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">created</span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.75pt"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">to</span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.7pt"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">solve</span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.75pt"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">this </span>problem. It was a W3C recommendation.
			</p>
