			<p style="margin:0.05pt 5.85pt 0pt 23pt; text-align:justify; line-height:106%; font-size:12pt">
				<span style="font-family:'Arial Black'; letter-spacing:-0.4pt">Declaration</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Black'; letter-spacing:-0.6pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Arial Black'; letter-spacing:-0.4pt">Block:</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Black'"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.4pt">The declaration block can</span> <span style="letter-spacing:-0.4pt">contain one</span> <span style="letter-spacing:-0.4pt">or more declarations separated </span>by a semicolon. For the above example, there are two declarations:
