			<h1 style="margin-top:5.3pt; margin-left:23pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-align:justify; font-size:22pt">
				CSS<span style="letter-spacing:-1pt"> </span>font-<span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">weight</span>
			</h1>
			<p style="margin:15.7pt 5.75pt 0pt 23pt; text-align:justify; line-height:116%; font-size:12pt">
				This<span style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt"> </span>property<span style="letter-spacing:-0.6pt"> </span>is<span style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt"> </span>used<span style="letter-spacing:-0.6pt"> </span>for<span style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt"> </span>setting<span style="letter-spacing:-0.6pt"> </span>the<span style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt"> </span>thickness<span style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt"> </span>and<span style="letter-spacing:-0.6pt"> </span>boldness<span style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt"> </span>of<span style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt"> </span>the<span style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt"> </span>font.<span style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt"> </span>It<span style="letter-spacing:-0.6pt"> </span>is<span style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt"> </span>used<span style="letter-spacing:-0.6pt"> </span>to<span style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt"> </span>define the<span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt"> </span>weight of<span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt"> </span>the<span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt"> </span>text. The<span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt"> </span>available weight depends<span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt"> </span>on<span style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt"> </span>the<span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt"> </span>font-family, which<span style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt"> </span>is<span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt"> </span>used by the browser.
			</p>
			<p style="margin-top:11.95pt; margin-left:23pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt">
				<span style="font-family:'Arial Black'; letter-spacing:-0.1pt">Syntax</span>
