				CSS<span style="letter-spacing:-0.5pt"> </span>Line<span style="letter-spacing:-0.5pt"> </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt">Height</span>
			</h1>
			<p style="margin-top:13.8pt; margin-left:23pt; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:106%; font-size:12pt">
				<span style="letter-spacing:-0.4pt">The</span> <span style="font-family:'Arial Black'; letter-spacing:-0.4pt">CSS</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Black'; letter-spacing:-0.8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Arial Black'; letter-spacing:-0.4pt">line</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Black'; letter-spacing:-0.8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Arial Black'; letter-spacing:-0.4pt">height</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Black'; letter-spacing:-0.8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Arial Black'; letter-spacing:-0.4pt">property </span><span style="letter-spacing:-0.4pt">is used</span> <em><span style="letter-spacing:-0.4pt">to define the minimal height of line boxes within the </span></em><em>element</em>. It sets the differences between two lines of your content.
			</p>
			<p style="margin-top:1.55pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt">
				&#xa0;
			</p>
			<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-left:23pt; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:116%; font-size:12pt">
				It defines the amount of space above and below inline elements. It allows you to set the height of a line of independently from the font size.
			</p>
			<h3 style="margin-top:12.15pt; margin-left:23pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:19pt">
				<span style="font-weight:normal">CSS</span><span style="font-weight:normal; letter-spacing:-0.8pt"> </span><span style="font-weight:normal">line-height</span><span style="font-weight:normal; letter-spacing:-0.8pt"> </span><span style="font-weight:normal; letter-spacing:-0.1pt">values</span>
			</h3>
