			<h3 style="margin-top:0pt; margin-left:23pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:19pt">
				<span style="font-weight:normal">Difference</span><span style="font-weight:normal; letter-spacing:-0.75pt"> </span><span style="font-weight:normal">between</span><span style="font-weight:normal; letter-spacing:-0.75pt"> </span><span style="font-weight:normal">Border</span><span style="font-weight:normal; letter-spacing:-0.6pt"> </span><span style="font-weight:normal">and</span><span style="font-weight:normal; letter-spacing:-0.7pt"> </span><span style="font-weight:normal; letter-spacing:-0.1pt">Outline</span>
			</h3>
			<p style="margin:15.55pt 6.2pt 0pt 23pt; text-align:justify; line-height:116%; font-size:12pt">
				<span style="color:#333333">At first glance, border and outline look similar, but there are some very important differences between them:</span>
