			<p style="margin-top:2.45pt; margin-bottom:0pt">
				&#xa0;
			</p>
			<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-left:23pt; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:116%; font-size:12pt">
				<span style="color:#333333">A CSS layout can have header, footer, left pane, right pane and body part. Let's see a simple example of </span><a href="https://www.javatpoint.com/css-tutorial" style="text-decoration:none"><u><span style="color:#008000">CSS</span></u></a><span style="color:#008000"> </span><span style="color:#333333">layout.</span>
			</p>
		</div>
		<br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both; mso-break-type:section-break" >
		<div>
			<p style="margin-top:3.05pt; margin-left:23pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:19pt">
